com.datapak.shopify_java_api.model

Class Order

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.datapak.shopify_java_api.model.ShopifyObject
      • com.datapak.shopify_java_api.model.Order

  • public class Order
extends ShopifyObject
    Represents a Shopify Order An order is a customer's completed request to purchase one or more products from a shop. An order is created when a customer completes the checkout process, during which time s/he provides an email address or phone number, billing address and payment information.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    jbrown

      • getCancel_reason

        public String getCancel_reason()
        Gets the reason why the order was cancelled. If the order was not cancelled, the value will be on of the following: customer: The customer changed cancelled the order fraud: The order was fradulent inventory: Items in the order were not in inventory other: The order was cancelled for a reason not in the list above
        Returns:
        A String containing the reason why the order was cancelled

      • setCancel_reason

        public void setCancel_reason(String cancel_reason)
        Sets the reason why the order was cancelled. If the order was not cancelled, the value will be on of the following: customer: The customer changed cancelled the order fraud: The order was fradulent inventory: Items in the order were not in inventory other: The order was cancelled for a reason not in the list above
        Parameters:
        cancel_reason - The reason why the order was cancelled
